2><p class=3D"Text_m-SansReg__eVOGe" style=3D"direction:ltr"><span style=3D=
"font-size:undefined">Cooking times can vary significantly depending on the=
 method used. Whether you're preparing meat for </span><a class=3D"RichText=
_anchor__bEdSD" href=3D"https://www.instacart.com/company/ideas/ground-turk=
ey-recipes/"><span style=3D"font-size:undefined">ground turkey recipes</spa=
n></a><span style=3D"font-size:undefined"> or grilling chicken for baked di=
shes, understanding how to adjust times ensures your meat is cooked to perf=
ection. Here are a few tips to keep in mind.</span></p><h3 class=3D"Text_xl=
-ContrastSemi__1vI_l"><b class=3D"RichText_bold__GUmsN">Oven roasting vs. g=
rilling or smoking</b><span style=3D"color:rgb(67, 67, 67)"><b class=3D"Ric=
hText_bold__GUmsN">&nbsp;</b></span></h3><p class=3D"Text_m-SansReg__eVOGe"=
 style=3D"direction:ltr"><span style=3D"font-size:undefined">When making a =
chicken or </span><a class=3D"RichText_anchor__bEdSD" href=3D"https://www.i=
nstacart.com/company/ideas/beef-roast-all-you-need-to-know/"><span style=3D=
"font-size:undefined">beef roast</span></a><span style=3D"font-size:undefin=
ed"> in the oven, cooking durations will differ based on temperature and we=
ight. A general rule of thumb is about 20 minutes per pound for poultry at =
350=C2=B0F, while beef roasts typically require 18-22 minutes per pound at =
the same temperature.</span></p><p class=3D"Text_m-SansReg__eVOGe" style=3D=
"direction:ltr"><span style=3D"font-size:undefined">For grilling, cooking t=
imes are usually faster, reducing the oven-based time by approximately 25%.=
 That means if a recipe calls for 20 minutes per pound in the oven, you sho=
uld start checking for doneness around 15 minutes per pound. Smoking, on th=
e other hand, involves low temperatures (225-250=C2=B0F) and takes 30 to 40=
 minutes longer per pound for larger cuts like brisket or pork shoulder for=
 </span><a class=3D"RichText_anchor__bEdSD" href=3D"https://www.instacart.c=
om/company/ideas/pork-chop-recipe-ideas/"><span style=3D"font-size:undefine=
d">pork chop recipes</span></a><span style=3D"font-size:undefined">.</span>=
</p><h3 class=3D"Text_xl-ContrastSemi__1vI_l"><b class=3D"RichText_bold__GU=
msN">Pressure cooker and slow cooker considerations</b><span style=3D"color=
:rgb(67, 67, 67)"><b class=3D"RichText_bold__GUmsN">&nbsp;</b></span></h3><=
p class=3D"Text_m-SansReg__eVOGe" style=3D"direction:ltr"><span style=3D"fo=
nt-size:undefined">Pressure cookers cook meat quickly under pressure, often=
 reducing traditional cooking times by up to 50%. Slow cookers, on the othe=
r hand, require longer, low-temperature cooking, generally 4 to 8 hours bas=
